  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How much does it cost to learn at Oxford aviation academy?",
  "response": "The cost of training at Oxford Aviation Academy (now known as CAE Oxford Aviation Academy) can vary depending on the specific course and location you choose. However, I can provide you with a general idea of the costs associated with some of their popular programs.\n\n1. **Integrated Airline Transport Pilot Licence (ATPL) Program:**\n   - This program typically takes around 18 months to complete.\n   - The cost can range from approximately \u00a3100,000 to \u00a3130,000. This includes all training, exams, and accommodation.\n\n2. **Modular ATPL Program:**\n   - This program allows you to complete the training at your own pace.\n   - Costs can vary widely based on the modules you choose and the time you take to complete them. On average, the total cost can range from \u00a360,000 to \u00a390,000.\n\n3. **Multi-Crew Pilot Licence (MPL) Program:**\n   - This program is often sponsored by airlines and includes type rating for a specific aircraft.\n   - The cost can be around \u00a380,000 to \u00a3100,000 if not sponsored, but many students receive sponsorship which can significantly reduce out-of-pocket expenses.\n\n4. **Type Rating Courses:**\n   - These courses are for pilots who already hold a commercial pilot license and want to fly a specific type of aircraft.\n   - Costs can range from \u00a320,000 to \u00a335,000 depending on the aircraft type.\n\nPlease note that these figures are approximate and can change. It's always best to contact CAE Oxford Aviation Academy directly for the most current and accurate pricing information. Additionally, consider additional costs such as living expenses, visas, and other personal expenditures when budgeting for your training.",
